// Fires when sessions-hub logs hub.certs.orphan_revoke_failed within the last hour — a client cert the
// CA minted that the hub could neither record (queue into retired_certs) NOR revoke. It is the terminal
// "leaked live cert" signal: the renew orphan-reclaim path (a CAS conflict or post-sign D1 write
// failure), or the post-sign fingerprint failure (a malformed cert with an id but no fingerprint to
// queue under), tried a direct CA revoke and it did NOT confirm — either the DELETE threw, or it
// returned HTTP-200 {success:false} (surfaced as revokeClientCert -> 'failed'). Left alone the cert
// stays valid at the CA, untracked in both `machines` and `retired_certs`, burning zone quota and — if
// its fingerprint were ever reused — a potential impersonation handle. Each event should be
// investigated: revoke the cert by its id manually.
//
// Configure the scheduled-query rule to fire on count >= 1 over the window (each leaked cert is
// individually actionable). Distinct from hub.certs.cf_auth_failed (which means the TOKEN is dead —
// every operation fails); an orphan leak can happen with a perfectly healthy OAuth grant (transient D1, a
// CAS race, a malformed CF payload), so it gets its own alert.
//
// The event { machine, cert_id, result?/error? } is emitted by revokeOrphanCert() in
// hub/src/api/certs.ts. hub.certs.orphan_queue_failed (the queue INSERT failing) is NOT alerted on its
// own — it is followed by the direct revoke, and only if THAT also fails does orphan_revoke_failed fire.
//
// See missed-heartbeat.kql for the OTelLogs/Body-as-JSON assumption this query shares. ASSUMPTION TO
// VERIFY AT M4 DEPLOY: confirm the table/column names once real data flows.

// `otel` wraps OTelLogs in `union isfuzzy=true` so a missing table (before the first OTLP log lands)
// degrades to empty instead of erroring the whole rule — see missed-heartbeat.kql's "Missing-table
// guard" note for the full rationale.
let otel = union isfuzzy=true
    (datatable(TimeGenerated:datetime, Body:string)[]),
    (OTelLogs | project TimeGenerated, Body);
otel
| where TimeGenerated > ago(1h)
| extend body = todynamic(Body)
| where body.event == "hub.certs.orphan_revoke_failed"
| extend machine = tostring(body.machine), cert_id = tostring(body.cert_id), result = tostring(body.result), error = tostring(body.error)
| project TimeGenerated, machine, cert_id, result, error
